		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    magicians a great class</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:daman-218@hotmail.com">heckios</a> | 
		            7/20/2000 12:45:09 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">magicians are generally decided to be the best pure caster class, and i don't agree. I originally started out with a wizard, then i switched to a mage. Mage's are great dont get me wrong but first off the pet is nice if not useless in some situations, also a distinct lack of dd spells makes for a hard timeif your out of malachites or lapis lazulis. also as a mage i get constantly peastered to summon ppl food, ppl i don't even know. So for all you newbie mages out there try these tips. 1. only summon food for ppl you know or are in your group, other wise you get to be known as charity man and you never get to play. 2. only use the water anf earth elemental, fire and air have to low of hit points to make it worth while also keep a healthy supply of malachites on you i cant express this enough.3 Never kill steal this is easy for a mage, ppl will hate you. <BR>
<BR>
Training areas: <BR>
Lvl 1-4<BR>
I started as a high elf so i reccomend the greater faydark. YOu can hunt really close to felwithe and still lvl up quickly.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 4-10<BR>
<BR>
East Commons at lower levels you can hunt bears then aroundlvl 7 you can start the orc camps.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 10-13<BR>
<BR>
North Ro, stick to the derv camps and you will generally lvl up quickly, also cutthroat insignia rings are valuable to you giving you an intelligence bonus.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 13-17<BR>
<BR>
The orc Highway in the oasis of marr. Here there are lots of groups and lots of combat which means fast lvl ups.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 17-19<BR>
<BR>
High pass Hold is a great place to get experience and valuable loot, you can enjoy easy combat and decent exp.<BR>
<BR>
Lvl 19-22 <BR>
<BR>
The rathe mountains are a nice place to hunt good combat decent groups. From my experience I usually got a lvl up in one night there until i hit lvl. 22
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
