			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I would disagree a bit. First mage gets the second best dd spells in the game next to a wizard. Pet's are a great addition and I'm not sure in what situations you would consider them worthless. Earth and Water are solo pets and how you play depends on which you choose.  The air and fire are situation specific.  The air is a great group pet.  It's stun interupt casters and on non casters will give a warrior an extra round to hit during the stun.  The fire deals real damage in a group at lower levels.  Since pets are at the bottom of the list for mobs to address when you are in a group the fire pet does not get hit often so low HP are not an issue.  At higher levels the damage shield on a fire pet is very significant and can take down blue mobs.  You really need to play the class and try things out to really understand it.  Might not be the best class but it's somewhere near the top of the list.
				</font>
			</td>

